\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 This is not a coincidence.
 In more advanced classes we study the case that both 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 are random, and in particular, when they are jointly normally distributed.
\end_layout

